1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 4. Nc3 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. e4 g6 7. f4
{ We shall now cover White's most aggressive systems where he launches an early pawn storm. }
7... Bg7 8. e5
{ White goes straight for the throat but runs a huge risk of being overextended. }
8... Nfd7 9. Nb5 { This is more testing than  9.e6. } 9... dxe5
{ The only move. Black should not allow White's knight on d6 to be supported by a f4-e5 pawn chain with   9...O-O?  10.Nxd6. }
10. Nd6+ Ke7 { Black should immediately challenge the d6-knight. } 11. Nxc8+
Qxc8 12. d6+ Kf8 13. Nf3
{ White is trying to coax Black into playing  13...exf4  14.Bxf4  , when he would maybe have something to show for his sacrificed material. }
13... Nc6
{ Simply developing and maintaining control over the d4- and e5-squares. } 14.
Be2 e4 { Now the f3-knight has no good square to move to. } *

