14. Nc4 { White chases the queen away from her strong b6-square. } 14... Qa6
{ Normally c4 is an excellent square for White's knight in the Benoni, but in this position it lacks support - White cannot play b2-b3 and it is awkward for him to protect the knight in other ways. }
15. Qe2 Nd7 16. Rd1 Nf6
{ Black's position is easy to play, as the bishops will dominate the a1-h8 and h1-a8 diagonals while White has various weaknesses to attend to. }
