13. Bf4 Nh5 14. Be3 c4
{ Distracting the bishop looks like an interesting play here. } 15. Bxc4
{ Best seems  15.a3  Bxf3  16.axb4   16.Bxf3  Nd3 !  16...Bxe2  17.Rxe2  and now Black could try  17...Be5  followed by ...Qh4 or ...Qd7-g4, probing the kingside. }
15... Bxf3 16. gxf3 Qh4
{ Black has a strong attack - he can follow up with ...Be5 and ...Nf4. Again, the trade of the c8-bishop for the f3-knight increases our control over the dark squares. }
