[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 4. Nc3 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. e4 g6 7. Nf3 Bg7 8. Be2
{ This is the starting position of the classical mainline. White wants to O-O, play ♘d2-c4, restrain the queenside and eventually play f2-f4, getting a better version of the positional Four Pawns Attack. }
8... O-O { As usual we start with castling and putting a rook on e8. } 9. O-O
Re8 { e4 is hanging. } 10. Nd2 Nbd7 11. a4
{ White can maintain the queen at d1 and play a sort of waiting game with Re1, h2-h3 and Nf1 to follow. Here Black can enjoy easy play with ...a6/...Rb8/...Ne5 and keep an eye on the h5 square for an eventual ...Nh5. }
11... a6 12. Re1 Rb8 13. Ra3
{ A creative rook lift that has had success against the Benoni. } 13... Ne5 14.
Nf1 Nh5 { An outlandish and provocative move! } 15. f4
{ This is also very likely to occur. } 15... Nd7
{ There is no shame in this retreat. We have provoked White to expose his jugular! }
16. Bxh5
{ White feels that it is safe to grab a pawn on h5, but Black says: not so fast... }
16... b5 { I want to see the look on their face after this one! } 17. axb5 axb5
18. Ne2 { This is the best move according to the machine. } 18... gxh5
{ We do have to regain our piece at some point. } 19. Neg3 Bd4+
{ An important nuance to create an interference with the rook along the 3rd rank. }
20. Be3 Bxb2 21. Nxh5 { Be on your guard! White prepares a mate. } 21... Nf6
22. Rb3 Nxh5 23. Qxh5
{ Correctly played. Now Black will get a bit of his own medicine so care must be taken. }
23... Bg7 24. Bd2
{ Preparing the second wave with Rg3. Instead,   24.Bf2  allows Black to play  24...Qf6  with a complex game. }
24... Bd4+ { Again the interference defense. } 25. Kh1 { 25.Be3  Bg7 = } 25...
Kh8 26. f5
{ Playing directly for mate. If White had snatched the pawn with  26.Qxf7  then Black has the profound  26...Bg4 !  , suddenly cutting off the escape of White's queen and preparing to march the queenside pawns. }
26... f6
{ A key defensive clearing of the 7th rank for defense. The positions remains ultra sharp but Black has excellent play. }
