[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 4. Nc3 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. Nf3 g6 7. Bf4
{ This simple developing move is more popular than 7. Nd2. } 7... Bg7 8. e3
{ This is a much quieter system. White just wants to put his dark-squared bishop outside the pawn chain and finish development. Note that  8.h3  will usually tranpose after  8...O-O  9.e3. }
8... O-O 9. h3 { White first secures the bishop's escape before playing Nd2. }
9... Qe7
{ This move signals that Black is interested in advancing the f-pawn and keeping the rook at f8. }
10. Nd2 { This appears to be a mistake. } 10... Nh5 11. Bh2 f5 12. Be2 f4
{ Black's attack comes first, releasing the pent up energy of the Benoni horde. }
13. Bxh5 fxe3 14. O-O exd2 15. Be2 Bh6 16. f4 Qe3+ 17. Kh1 Nd7 18. Bg1 Qg3
{ It is not so easy to chase off the pesky Black queen. } *

