[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "13. Saemisch"]
[Black "123. Saemisch: 7. Nge2 system"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 4. Nc3 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. e4 g6 7. Nge2
{ This is a cousin of the Saemisch. It leads to positions that are similar to the ones after  7.f3  , but Black should know the exact counter. }
7... Bg7 8. Ng3 a6 9. a4 h5
{ Now Black gains the option of kicking away the g3-knight with a timely ...h4. }
10. Be2 Qe7
{ This is an interesting attempt to force White into playing f2-f3 to protect the e4-pawn. }
11. Bg5 Qe5 12. Qd2 h4 13. Bf4 Qe7 14. Nf1 h3
{ Forcing a weakening of the kingside. Black eventually won in the game Dreev, A.  2688  vs. Minasian, A.  2557  , Moscow 2009. }
*

