12. O-O h4 { With the rook on h8 this advance gains in strength. } 13. Nh1 Nh5
{ Preventing Bg5 and increasing our control over the dark squares. } 14. Nf2
Bd4 15. f4 Ng3
{ A clever move. White cannot take due to mate down the h-file. } 16. Re1 g5
{ I don't know about you but I like the direction things are going here for Black. }
